race.comment: Sticking with MAGNA'S CHOICE (4). Won his first two career starts then was beaten just a length in stakes class. Had just one run last time in and was a close-up third. Fitter for the two trials and on what he's shown in limited starts so far is the one to beat if presented on song. SPARKLE CORNER (8) is also back from a break. Fitter for two trials and is a speedy type who has placed fresh. Can give a sight. PURE EXCESS (11) placed in both runs in first campaign before another break. Sure to have improved and will be fitter for the one trial. Light weight and low draw for return and worth keeping safe. CLEANEMUP (2) has been thereabouts and was solid in a richer race last time. Senior rider back on and worth another try. INVINCIBLE POWER (3) resumes from a long spell. Fitter for the one trial and placed only try at course and distance. Pike aboard and worth keeping safe.
